# Normalise every text file to LF, in the repository and in the working tree,
# on every platform. This working tree is synced with Syncthing across Windows,
# macOS, and Linux, so the bytes on disk must match everywhere. Mixed CRLF/LF
# endings show up as phantom diffs and cause Syncthing conflicts; forcing LF
# stops both. Git auto-detects binary files and leaves them untouched.
* text=auto eol=lf
